---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Design a Ride-Sharing Service — Interactive Visualization"
  description="Understand ride-sharing architecture: driver matching, geospatial indexing, ETA calculation, surge pricing. Interactive simulation."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { label: "Home", href: "/" },
    { label: "System Design", href: "/system-design/" },
    { label: "Ride Sharing", href: "/system-design/ride-sharing/" }
  ]}
>
  <div class="viz-container">
    <header class="viz-header">
      <h1>🚗 Design a Ride-Sharing Service</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Driver matching, geospatial indexing, ETA calculation, and surge pricing — interactive exploration</p>
    </header>

    <section class="overview-section">
      <div class="overview-card">
        <p>
          A ride-sharing service like Uber or Lyft connects <strong>riders</strong> with nearby <strong>drivers</strong> in real time.
          The core challenges: <strong>efficient driver matching</strong> using geospatial indexes,
          <strong>accurate ETA calculation</strong> factoring in traffic and road networks,
          <strong>dynamic surge pricing</strong> to balance supply and demand,
          and <strong>scaling to millions</strong> of concurrent rides across cities worldwide.
          This page explores each component interactively.
        </p>
        <div class="overview-stats">
          <div class="stat-item">
            <span class="stat-value">~20M</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Daily trips (Uber)</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-item">
            <span class="stat-value">&lt;3s</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Match latency target</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-item">
            <span class="stat-value">~5M</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Active drivers</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-item">
            <span class="stat-value">10K+</span>
            <span class="stat-label">Cities served</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 1: Interactive Map with Driver Matching -->
    <section class="controls-section">
      <h2>🗺️ Interactive Map — Driver Matching</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Click on the map to place a <strong>rider</strong>, then click <strong>Find Nearest Driver</strong> to watch the matching algorithm in action. Drivers are shown as blue dots. The matched driver highlights green with an animated route.</p>
      <div class="map-controls">
        <button id="placeRiderBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">📍 Place Rider (click map)</button>
        <button id="matchDriverBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary" disabled>🔍 Find Nearest Driver</button>
        <button id="resetMapBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">🔄 Reset Map</button>
        <button id="addDriverBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">➕ Add Random Driver</button>
      </div>
      <div class="map-wrapper">
        <canvas id="mapCanvas" width="800" height="500"></canvas>
        <div id="mapInfo" class="map-info-panel">
          <div class="info-row"><span class="info-label">Rider Position:</span> <span id="riderPos">Not placed</span></div>
          <div class="info-row"><span class="info-label">Drivers Nearby:</span> <span id="driverCount">0</span></div>
          <div class="info-row"><span class="info-label">Matched Driver:</span> <span id="matchedDriver">—</span></div>
          <div class="info-row"><span class="info-label">Distance:</span> <span id="matchDistance">—</span></div>
          <div class="info-row"><span class="info-label">Match Time:</span> <span id="matchTime">—</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div id="distanceList" class="distance-list"></div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 2: Geospatial Indexing -->
    <section class="controls-section">
      <h2>🌐 Geospatial Indexing Visualization</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Ride-sharing services need to quickly find nearby drivers. Two common approaches: <strong>Quadtree</strong> (recursive spatial subdivision) and <strong>Geohash</strong> (hierarchical grid cells with string-based hashing). Toggle between views below.</p>
      <div class="geo-toggle">
        <button id="quadtreeViewBtn" class="action-btn toggle-btn active">Quadtree</button>
        <button id="geohashViewBtn" class="action-btn toggle-btn">Geohash</button>
      </div>
      <div class="geo-controls">
        <button id="addGeoPointBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">➕ Add Driver</button>
        <button id="removeGeoPointBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">➖ Remove Last</button>
        <button id="clearGeoBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">🗑️ Clear All</button>
        <button id="bulkAddBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">⚡ Add 20 Drivers</button>
      </div>
      <div class="geo-wrapper">
        <canvas id="geoCanvas" width="600" height="600"></canvas>
        <div class="geo-info-panel">
          <h4 id="geoInfoTitle">Quadtree Info</h4>
          <div class="info-row"><span class="info-label">Total Points:</span> <span id="geoPointCount">0</span></div>
          <div class="info-row"><span class="info-label">Tree Depth:</span> <span id="geoDepth">0</span></div>
          <div class="info-row"><span class="info-label">Leaf Nodes:</span> <span id="geoLeaves">0</span></div>
          <div id="geoExplanation" class="geo-explanation">
            <p><strong>Quadtree:</strong> The space is recursively divided into 4 quadrants. When a quadrant has more than <code>MAX_POINTS</code> drivers, it splits. Searching for nearby drivers only examines relevant quadrants — O(log n) instead of O(n).</p>
          </div>
          <div id="geohashInfo" class="geo-explanation" style="display:none;">
            <p><strong>Geohash:</strong> The map is divided into grid cells, each identified by a base32 string. Nearby locations share common prefixes. To find nearby drivers, query the same cell and its 8 neighbors. Precision level controls cell size.</p>
            <div class="geohash-precision">
              <label>Precision Level: <span id="precisionVal">4</span></label>
              <input type="range" id="precisionSlider" min="2" max="6" value="4" step="1">
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 3: ETA Calculation -->
    <section class="controls-section">
      <h2>⏱️ ETA Calculation Pipeline</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">ETA goes through multiple refinement stages. Drag the <strong>driver</strong> (blue) and <strong>rider</strong> (red) markers on the mini-map. Adjust traffic and road network factors with the sliders to see how ETA changes in real time.</p>
      <div class="eta-layout">
        <div class="eta-map-col">
          <canvas id="etaCanvas" width="400" height="400"></canvas>
          <div class="eta-positions">
            <span class="eta-legend driver-legend">● Driver</span>
            <span class="eta-legend rider-legend">● Rider</span>
            <span class="eta-note">Drag markers to reposition</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="eta-pipeline-col">
          <div class="eta-stage" id="etaStage1">
            <div class="stage-header">
              <span class="stage-num">1</span>
              <span class="stage-title">Straight-Line Distance</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-value" id="etaStraight">—</div>
            <div class="stage-desc">Haversine / Euclidean distance between driver and rider</div>
          </div>
          <div class="eta-arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="eta-stage" id="etaStage2">
            <div class="stage-header">
              <span class="stage-num">2</span>
              <span class="stage-title">Road Network Adjustment</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-value" id="etaRoad">—</div>
            <div class="stage-desc">
              Multiply by road factor:
              <input type="range" id="roadFactor" min="1.1" max="2.0" step="0.1" value="1.4">
              <span id="roadFactorVal">1.4x</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="eta-arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="eta-stage" id="etaStage3">
            <div class="stage-header">
              <span class="stage-num">3</span>
              <span class="stage-title">Traffic Adjustment</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-value" id="etaTraffic">—</div>
            <div class="stage-desc">
              Traffic multiplier:
              <input type="range" id="trafficFactor" min="1.0" max="3.0" step="0.1" value="1.2">
              <span id="trafficFactorVal">1.2x</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="eta-arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="eta-stage" id="etaStage4">
            <div class="stage-header">
              <span class="stage-num">4</span>
              <span class="stage-title">Historical Data Correction</span>
            </div>
            <div class="stage-value" id="etaHistorical">—</div>
            <div class="stage-desc">
              ML model correction:
              <input type="range" id="historicalFactor" min="0.8" max="1.3" step="0.05" value="1.0">
              <span id="historicalFactorVal">1.0x</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="eta-arrow">↓</div>
          <div class="eta-final">
            <span class="final-label">Final ETA</span>
            <span class="final-value" id="etaFinal">—</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 4: Surge Pricing -->
    <section class="controls-section">
      <h2>💰 Surge Pricing Visualization</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">When demand exceeds supply, surge pricing kicks in. Click on the heat map to <strong>increase demand</strong> in that area. Watch the surge multiplier update dynamically. The formula: <code>surge = max(1.0, demand / supply * weight)</code>.</p>
      <div class="surge-controls">
        <button id="surgeResetBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">🔄 Reset</button>
        <button id="surgeRainBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">🌧️ Rain Event (+demand)</button>
        <button id="surgeConcertBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">🎵 Concert Ends (+demand)</button>
        <div class="surge-supply-ctrl">
          <label>Base Supply Level: <span id="supplyVal">50</span></label>
          <input type="range" id="supplySlider" min="10" max="100" value="50" step="5">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="surge-layout">
        <div class="surge-map-col">
          <canvas id="surgeCanvas" width="500" height="500"></canvas>
          <div class="surge-legend">
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-color" style="background:#22c55e"></span>1.0x</span>
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-color" style="background:#eab308"></span>1.5x</span>
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-color" style="background:#f97316"></span>2.0x</span>
            <span class="legend-item"><span class="legend-color" style="background:#ef4444"></span>2.5x+</span>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="surge-info-col">
          <div class="surge-stat">
            <span class="surge-stat-label">Avg Surge Multiplier</span>
            <span class="surge-stat-value" id="avgSurge">1.0x</span>
          </div>
          <div class="surge-stat">
            <span class="surge-stat-label">Max Surge</span>
            <span class="surge-stat-value" id="maxSurge">1.0x</span>
          </div>
          <div class="surge-stat">
            <span class="surge-stat-label">Total Demand</span>
            <span class="surge-stat-value" id="totalDemand">0</span>
          </div>
          <div class="surge-stat">
            <span class="surge-stat-label">Total Supply</span>
            <span class="surge-stat-value" id="totalSupply">0</span>
          </div>
          <div class="surge-formula">
            <h4>Pricing Formula</h4>
            <code>base_fare = $2.50 + $1.75/mile + $0.35/min</code><br>
            <code>final_fare = base_fare × surge_multiplier</code><br>
            <div class="surge-example" id="surgeExample">
              <p>Example: 5-mile, 15-min ride</p>
              <p>Base: $2.50 + $8.75 + $5.25 = <strong>$16.50</strong></p>
              <p>With 1.0x surge: <strong id="surgeFareExample">$16.50</strong></p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 5: Trip Lifecycle State Machine -->
    <section class="controls-section">
      <h2>🔄 Trip Lifecycle — State Machine</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">A ride goes through multiple stages from request to rating. Click <strong>Next Step</strong> to advance through the lifecycle. Each state triggers specific backend operations.</p>
      <div class="lifecycle-controls">
        <button id="lifecycleNextBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn">▶ Next Step</button>
        <button id="lifecycleResetBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">🔄 Reset</button>
        <button id="lifecycleAutoBtn" class="action-btn primary-btn-secondary">⏩ Auto-Play</button>
      </div>
      <div class="lifecycle-wrapper">
        <div class="lifecycle-states">
          <div class="lc-state" data-state="request" id="lcRequest">
            <div class="lc-icon">📱</div>
            <div class="lc-name">Request</div>
          </div>
          <div class="lc-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="lc-state" data-state="matching" id="lcMatching">
            <div class="lc-icon">🔍</div>
            <div class="lc-name">Matching</div>
          </div>
          <div class="lc-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="lc-state" data-state="enroute" id="lcEnroute">
            <div class="lc-icon">🚗</div>
            <div class="lc-name">En Route</div>
          </div>
          <div class="lc-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="lc-state" data-state="pickup" id="lcPickup">
            <div class="lc-icon">📍</div>
            <div class="lc-name">Pickup</div>
          </div>
          <div class="lc-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="lc-state" data-state="intrip" id="lcIntrip">
            <div class="lc-icon">🛣️</div>
            <div class="lc-name">In Trip</div>
          </div>
          <div class="lc-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="lc-state" data-state="dropoff" id="lcDropoff">
            <div class="lc-icon">🏁</div>
            <div class="lc-name">Dropoff</div>
          </div>
          <div class="lc-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="lc-state" data-state="payment" id="lcPayment">
            <div class="lc-icon">💳</div>
            <div class="lc-name">Payment</div>
          </div>
          <div class="lc-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="lc-state" data-state="rating" id="lcRating">
            <div class="lc-icon">⭐</div>
            <div class="lc-name">Rating</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="lc-details" id="lcDetails">
          <div class="lc-detail-title" id="lcDetailTitle">Click "Next Step" to begin</div>
          <div class="lc-detail-body" id="lcDetailBody">
            <p>The trip lifecycle follows a strict state machine. Each transition triggers specific backend operations, notifications, and data updates.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="lc-backend-ops" id="lcBackendOps"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 6: Architecture Deep Dive -->
    <section class="controls-section">
      <h2>🏗️ Architecture Deep Dive</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">The ride-sharing platform is composed of many microservices working in concert. Click on any component to learn more about its design and scaling challenges.</p>
      <div class="arch-diagram">
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer-label">Client Layer</div>
          <div class="arch-nodes">
            <div class="arch-node client-node" data-component="rider-app">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">📱</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Rider App</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node client-node" data-component="driver-app">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">🚗</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Driver App</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-connector">↕ WebSocket / HTTPS</div>
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer-label">API Gateway & Load Balancer</div>
          <div class="arch-nodes">
            <div class="arch-node gateway-node" data-component="api-gateway">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">🌐</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">API Gateway</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-connector">↕</div>
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer-label">Core Services</div>
          <div class="arch-nodes">
            <div class="arch-node service-node" data-component="location-service">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">📡</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Location Tracking</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node service-node" data-component="matching-service">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">🔗</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Matching Engine</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node service-node" data-component="dispatch-service">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">📋</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Dispatch</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node service-node" data-component="pricing-service">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">💲</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Pricing / Surge</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node service-node" data-component="eta-service">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">⏱️</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">ETA Service</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node service-node" data-component="payment-service">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">💳</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Payment</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="arch-connector">↕</div>
        <div class="arch-layer">
          <div class="arch-layer-label">Data Layer</div>
          <div class="arch-nodes">
            <div class="arch-node data-node" data-component="location-db">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">🗄️</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Redis (Location Cache)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node data-node" data-component="trip-db">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">🗃️</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">PostgreSQL (Trips)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node data-node" data-component="geo-index">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">🌍</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Geo Index (S2/H3)</div>
            </div>
            <div class="arch-node data-node" data-component="kafka-bus">
              <div class="arch-node-icon">📨</div>
              <div class="arch-node-name">Kafka (Events)</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="arch-detail-panel" id="archDetailPanel">
        <h4 id="archDetailTitle">Select a component above</h4>
        <div id="archDetailBody">
          <p>Click on any component in the architecture diagram to learn about its design, responsibilities, and scaling considerations.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 7: Scaling Strategy -->
    <section class="controls-section">
      <h2>📈 Scaling Strategies</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">A ride-sharing platform must handle millions of location updates per second, match riders in under 3 seconds, and maintain five-nines uptime.</p>
      <div class="scaling-cards">
        <div class="scaling-card">
          <h4>📡 Location Tracking</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Drivers send GPS pings every <strong>3-4 seconds</strong></li>
            <li>5M drivers × 0.25 updates/sec = <strong>1.25M writes/sec</strong></li>
            <li>Use <strong>Redis Geo</strong> or <strong>in-memory store</strong> for current positions</li>
            <li>Shard by <strong>city + geohash prefix</strong></li>
            <li>TTL-based eviction for offline drivers</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="scaling-card">
          <h4>🔗 Matching Algorithm</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Nearest-neighbor</strong> as baseline, <strong>batch matching</strong> for optimization</li>
            <li>Consider driver heading, ETA, not just distance</li>
            <li>Batch window: 2-5 seconds to accumulate requests</li>
            <li><strong>Hungarian algorithm</strong> for optimal batch assignment</li>
            <li>Fallback to greedy matching under high load</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="scaling-card">
          <h4>🌐 Real-Time Communication</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>WebSocket</strong> connections for live updates</li>
            <li>Connection multiplexing via <strong>API gateway</strong></li>
            <li><strong>Server-Sent Events</strong> as fallback</li>
            <li>~10M concurrent WebSocket connections</li>
            <li>Use <strong>Pub/Sub</strong> for cross-server messaging</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="scaling-card">
          <h4>💳 Payment Processing</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Pre-authorize</strong> payment at ride request</li>
            <li><strong>Capture</strong> after trip completion</li>
            <li>Handle partial refunds, promo codes, split fares</li>
            <li><strong>Event sourcing</strong> for audit trail</li>
            <li>Idempotency keys prevent double charges</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="scaling-card">
          <h4>🗺️ Map & Routing</h4>
          <ul>
            <li>Use <strong>OSRM</strong> or custom routing engine</li>
            <li>Pre-compute routes for popular corridors</li>
            <li><strong>A* / Dijkstra</strong> on road graph</li>
            <li>Update traffic weights every 30-60 seconds</li>
            <li>Cache hot routes with short TTL</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="scaling-card">
          <h4>🛡️ Reliability</h4>
          <ul>
            <li><strong>Multi-region</strong> deployment per city cluster</li>
            <li>Circuit breakers between services</li>
            <li>Graceful degradation: simple matching if complex fails</li>
            <li><strong>Saga pattern</strong> for distributed transactions</li>
            <li>Ride state replicated across AZs</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Section 8: Key Design Decisions -->
    <section class="controls-section">
      <h2>⚖️ Key Design Decisions & Tradeoffs</h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Every design choice involves tradeoffs. Click on a card to explore the considerations.</p>
      <div class="tradeoff-cards">
        <div class="tradeoff-card" data-tradeoff="accuracy-speed">
          <div class="tradeoff-header">
            <span class="tradeoff-icon">🎯</span>
            <h4>Accuracy vs. Speed in Matching</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="tradeoff-body">
            <div class="tradeoff-side pro">
              <h5>Optimize for Accuracy</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Consider ETA, not just distance</li>
                <li>Factor in driver heading and route</li>
                <li>Batch requests for global optimum</li>
                <li>Better rider/driver experience</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tradeoff-side con">
              <h5>Optimize for Speed</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Simple nearest-driver wins</li>
                <li>Sub-second match time</li>
                <li>Less compute per match</li>
                <li>Lower perceived wait time</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tradeoff-verdict">
              <strong>In practice:</strong> Batch matching with a 2-3 second window achieves near-optimal matches while keeping latency acceptable.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tradeoff-card" data-tradeoff="fairness-efficiency">
          <div class="tradeoff-header">
            <span class="tradeoff-icon">⚖️</span>
            <h4>Fairness vs. Efficiency</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="tradeoff-body">
            <div class="tradeoff-side pro">
              <h5>Maximize Fairness</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Round-robin driver assignment</li>
                <li>Limit consecutive idle time</li>
                <li>Priority queue for longest-waiting</li>
                <li>Equal earning opportunity</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tradeoff-side con">
              <h5>Maximize Efficiency</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Always pick nearest driver</li>
                <li>Minimize empty miles</li>
                <li>Optimize fleet utilization</li>
                <li>Reduce rider wait times</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tradeoff-verdict">
              <strong>In practice:</strong> A hybrid approach — nearest-first with fairness constraints (e.g., max idle time before priority boost).
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tradeoff-card" data-tradeoff="realtime-batch">
          <div class="tradeoff-header">
            <span class="tradeoff-icon">⚡</span>
            <h4>Real-Time vs. Batch Processing</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="tradeoff-body">
            <div class="tradeoff-side pro">
              <h5>Real-Time Processing</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Instant match on each request</li>
                <li>Lower average latency</li>
                <li>Simpler implementation</li>
                <li>Better for low-demand areas</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tradeoff-side con">
              <h5>Batch Processing</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Accumulate requests over window</li>
                <li>Global optimization possible</li>
                <li>Better matches overall</li>
                <li>Higher throughput</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tradeoff-verdict">
              <strong>In practice:</strong> Use real-time for sparse areas, batch matching for dense urban zones where many requests arrive simultaneously.
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tradeoff-card" data-tradeoff="push-pull">
          <div class="tradeoff-header">
            <span class="tradeoff-icon">📡</span>
            <h4>Push vs. Pull for Location Updates</h4>
          </div>
          <div class="tradeoff-body">
            <div class="tradeoff-side pro">
              <h5>Push Model</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Drivers push updates on interval</li>
                <li>Server always has latest position</li>
                <li>Predictable write load</li>
                <li>Simple client implementation</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tradeoff-side con">
              <h5>Pull Model</h5>
              <ul>
                <li>Query driver location on demand</li>
                <li>Less bandwidth when idle</li>
                <li>Fresher data at query time</li>
                <li>Scales with reads not writes</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="tradeoff-verdict">
              <strong>In practice:</strong> Push model for active drivers (every 3-4s), with adaptive frequency based on driver state (slower when idle, faster during active trip).
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</BaseLayout>

